The paper deals with the problem of entity alignment between knowledge graphs, which is a common task in artificial intelligence and natural language processing. The proposed framework involves embedding entities based on multiple views, including entity names, relations, and attributes, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The use of cross-KG inference methods also suggests a focus on knowledge representation and reasoning, which is often studied in the subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the use of real-world datasets and evaluation metrics suggests a focus on data management and analysis, which is often studied in the subfield of database systems (cs.DB) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
